'_r_e_a_d_P_l_a_t_e_M_a_p'. _P_r_e-_d_e_f_i_n_e_d _r_e_a_d-_i_n _f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n_s _e_x_i_s_t _f_o_r _a _c_o_u_p_l_e _o_f
_p_l_a_t_e-_r_e_a_d_e_r_s.

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Parses data files in CSV, as exported by the plate reader
     software. Header IDs in the data file should match with IDs in the
     plate map, see ‘readPlateMap’. Pre-defined read-in functions exist
     for a couple of plate-readers.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     readPlateData(files, type, data.ids, skip = 0, sep = "\t", dec = ".",
       verb = TRUE, interpolate = TRUE, time.conversion, ...)
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

   files: list of one or more data files

    type: pre-defined formats, as exported from platereaders; currently
          for BMG Optima/Mars, ('BMG') and Synergy Mx ('Synergy').

data.ids: an optional sub-selection of data types in the input file, as
          a list of strings

    skip: lines to skip from the data file

     sep: column separator, as in read.table

     dec: decimal operator used in the data file

    verb: print messages if true

interpolate: if true a master time, the average time between distinct
          measurements of one timepoint, is calculated and all values
          are interpolated to this mastertime. This is currently
          obligatory for further processing.

time.conversion: conversion factor for the plate time, e.g., 1/3600 to
          convert from hours to seconds

     ...: further parameters to plate-reader specific parsing functions

_V_a_l_u_e:

     a list of distinct measurement time-courses from one plate

_N_o_t_e:

     The original data is all interpolated to a common/average 'master'
     time

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     Rainer Machne <email: raim@tbi.univie.ac.at>

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o:

     ‘readPlateMap’, ‘viewPlate’

_E_x_a_m_p_l_e_s:

     data.file <- system.file("extdata", "AP12.csv", package = "platexpress")
     raw <- readPlateData(files=data.file, type="Synergy", data.ids=c("600","YFP_50:500,535"), dec=",",time.format="%H:%M:%S")
     

